net.proteusframework.cms.component

Interface ContentElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    PageElement, Serializable, Trashable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractContentElement, ProxyServer

    public interface ContentElement
extends PageElement
    ContentElement. ContentElements should only be referenced from BeanBoxList and DelegateElement. A ContentElement is a specialization of PageElement that is meant to be used as a "Component" on a Page. The concept of a "Component" encapsulates the ContentElement implementation, the model it defines, the generators and renders it defines / uses, as well as the ContentElement editors that are associated to the ContentElement. ContentElement editors are configured by placing a PageElementModelConfiguration annotation on the ContentElement implementation class. In order for CMS to be able to find your "Component" / ContentElement, please provide a no-arg constructor.

    See CMS developement guide for information on creating a new ContentElement.

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)
